# Build & tooling

## Stack
- **Electron Forge** with the **Vite** plugin. One Vite config per context (main, preload, renderer) registered through Forge.
- TypeScript everywhere. No ts-node at runtime in production — everything is compiled by Vite.

## Scripts (package.json)
Expected scripts — adjust names if Forge defaults differ, but keep the semantics:
- `start` — `electron-forge start` (dev with HMR for renderer).
- `package` — produce an unsigned `.app` for local smoke-tests.
- `make` — produce the distributable (`.dmg` / `.zip`).
- `publish` — produce + upload (CI only).
- `lint` — ESLint over `src/`.
- `typecheck` — `tsc --noEmit` for each tsconfig.
- `test` — unit tests (Vitest preferred).

## Dependencies
- Native modules (anything with a `binding.gyp` or postinstall that builds): justify each one. They complicate signing and universal builds.
- Prefer pure-JS alternatives when they exist.
- Do not add a dependency without it being used. Do not add wrapper libraries for things Electron already does well.

## Dev workflow
- HMR is for renderer only. Changes to `main/` or `preload/` require a restart — Forge handles this.
- When changing IPC contracts, restart the dev server; HMR will not pick up preload changes reliably.

## Vite & in-repo workspace packages (IMPORTANT — bit us hard once)
- The renderer's `optimizeDeps.exclude` **MUST list every `@needle/*` workspace
  package the renderer imports** (`@needle/ui-web`, `@needle/domain`,
  `@needle/contract`) — see `apps/desktop/vite.renderer.config.ts`.
- Why: without it, Vite **pre-bundles** those packages into
  `node_modules/.vite/deps` and then serves that *frozen* copy. Edits to the
  package's source are then **silently ignored**, and a freshly-added export makes
  a normal `import { foo } from '@needle/ui-web'` throw at load time — a failed
  named import takes down the whole React mount, so the symptom is a **blank
  desktop window**, not an error in the UI. typecheck/tests stay green (they read
  source), which makes this very easy to misdiagnose.
- Excluding them serves the packages as live source with working HMR.
- Symptom → fix: ui-web/domain edits not appearing, or a blank renderer after
  adding an export → confirm the package is in `optimizeDeps.exclude`, then bust
  the cache: `rm -rf apps/desktop/node_modules/.vite` and restart `pnpm start`.
- Add any **new** renderer-consumed workspace package to that `exclude` list.

## Linting & formatting
- ESLint with `@typescript-eslint`, `eslint-plugin-react`, `eslint-plugin-react-hooks`, and an Electron-security plugin (`eslint-plugin-electron-security` or equivalent).
- Prettier with project defaults. Don't argue style in code review — let the formatter decide.
- Do not silence lint rules inline without a one-line reason. Don't disable rules project-wide to make a single file pass.
